            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An inner product on a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> over a field <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> (either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>) is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[<\cdot ,\cdot >: V \times  V \rightarrow  F]]></fr:tex> that satisfies the following properties for all vectors <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u, v, w \in  V]]></fr:tex> and all scalars <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \in  F]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:strong>Linearity in the first argument:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[<au + v, w> = a<u, w> + <v, w>]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Conjugate symmetry:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[<u, v> = \overline {<v, u>}]]></fr:tex> (where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {z}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0016.xml" addr="FA-0016" title="Conjugate">conjugate</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex>)</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Positive definiteness:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[<v, v> \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[<v, v> = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v = 0]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>An inner product induces a norm on the vector space via <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||v|| = \sqrt {<v, v>}]]></fr:tex>, which in turn defines a metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(u, v) = ||u - v||]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
